By Abiodun Lawal Abeokuta – An advocacy group, Concerned Parents and Educators (CPE), has lauded the Ogun government on its recent developmental policies aimed at revamping the state’s education sector. The group’s facilitator, Mrs Yinka Ogunde, stated this in Abeokuta during a visit to the State Commissioner for Education, Science and Technology, Prof. Sidi Osho. Ogunde noted that the group was founded with the aim of positively monitoring , impacting and contributing its quota to the education system in Nigeria. She stated that the group had successfully been able to positively influence school owners across the country as well as educate the less privileged children in some selected schools. Ogunde , while indicating the group’s readiness to work with the ministry, said she was particularly impressed with the state for declaring a state of emergency in the education sector. She said that the group was impressed with the state government over the improvement recorded so far in the education sector since it took over the mantle of governance. Responding , Osho said that she was delighted with the achievements of the current administration under the leadership of Gov. Dapo Abiodun in the sector. The commissioner explained that the state government was set to do more in ensuring that education in the state returned to its pride of place in the country. In her remarks, the Special Adviser to the Governor on Primary, Secondary and Technical Education, Mrs Ronke Soyombo, said that the governor was concerned about the condition of learners in schools as well as welfare of teachers. (NAN)